        experience during the period of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">February 2, 1994</TIMEX> to
        <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">December 28, 1995</TIMEX>. Firstly, this study was initiated to
        help to determine the causes of major <ENAMEX TYPE="DISEASE">morbidity</ENAMEX> and
        mortality after hepatobiliary surgery, such that we might
        alter our patient care in order to avoid similar
        complications in the future. <NUMEX TYPE="ORDINAL">Secondly</NUMEX>, this study was
        initiated to help to evaluate possible predictors of
        survival once a major complication had arisen, such that
        <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">guidance</ENAMEX> could be given to clinicians caring for such
        <ENAMEX TYPE="PER_DESC">patients</ENAMEX> in determining the likelihood of ultimate survival
